turbo.schemaDrift.tests.persistedValueShapesAreStable : [Result]
turbo.schemaDrift.tests.persistedValueShapesAreStable = test.verify do
  labeled "persisted value typed hashes match the approved schema baseline" do
    ensureEqual turbo.schemaDrift.expectedHashes turbo.schemaDrift.currentHashes
  labeled "persisted fixture values serialize to bytes that deserialize" do
    ensureEqual
      turbo.schemaDrift.expectedDeserializeChecks
      turbo.schemaDrift.currentDeserializeChecks

turbo.schemaDrift.check : '{Exception} ()
turbo.schemaDrift.check = do
  hashesMatch =
    Universal.eq turbo.schemaDrift.currentHashes turbo.schemaDrift.expectedHashes
  deserializeChecksPass =
    Universal.eq turbo.schemaDrift.currentDeserializeChecks turbo.schemaDrift.expectedDeserializeChecks
  if hashesMatch && deserializeChecksPass then
    ()
  else
    Exception.raiseGeneric
      "persisted backend value schema drift detected; approve a migration and update turbo.schemaDrift.expectedHashes"
      ( turbo.schemaDrift.expectedHashes
      , turbo.schemaDrift.currentHashes
      , turbo.schemaDrift.currentDeserializeChecks)

turbo.schemaDrift.doc : Doc
turbo.schemaDrift.doc =
  {{
  `turbo.schemaDrift` is the pre-deploy guard against accidental changes to backend values stored in Unison Cloud `OrderedTable`s.
  
  Each fixture is a known value for one persisted domain record. {{ docLink (docEmbedTermLink do turbo.schemaDrift.currentHashes) }} hashes those values with typed universal hashing, and {{ docLink (docEmbedTermLink do turbo.schemaDrift.expectedHashes) }} records the approved baseline. The guard also serializes each fixture to reflection bytes and verifies that those bytes deserialize. If a persisted type changes, {{ docLink (docEmbedTermLink do turbo.schemaDrift.check) }} fails before deploy.
  
  A failure means either the change must be reverted, the production data must be migrated or safely reset, or the new shape must be deliberately approved by updating `expectedHashes` in the same change. Runtime-only tables that store live refs or websockets are excluded because they are not ordinary portable durable values.
  }}
